<TITLE> New JP constitution bars associate bodies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com) - Jatiya Party on Sunday amended its constitution in line with new electoral laws, curbing the chairman's powers and barring the party from having student or professional bodies. Party chairman HM Ershad confirmed that JP would seek 60 seats from the Awami League-led grand alliance in the parliamentary election. Ershad was addressing a party executive committee that approved the amendment to the party constitution Party presidium member and chief of the committee on constitution amendment, GM Quader said they had made the changes in line with the new Representation of the People Ordinance. Quader said the amendment meant the JP chairman would not be able to hold the post for more than two terms, nor could the chairman take any decision without consulting with the party presidium. According to the amendment committees, from grassroots to the executive committee, would be formed through election. In line with the RPO, JP will not have any student or professional bodies, he added. Acting chairman barrister Anisul Islam Mahmud, presidium member Rowshan Ershad, Qazi Zafar Ahmed, secretary general ABM Ruhul Amin Hawlader also attended the meeting at Hotel Sundarban. bdnew
